NAME
       simple_shell - a minimal Unix command interpreter

SYNOPSIS
       simple_shell

DESCRIPTION
       simple_shell is a simple Unix command-line interpreter developed as part
       of the Holberton School curriculum. It provides a basic interface for
       users to execute commands and interact with the operating system.

COMMANDS
       The shell supports execution of external commands available in the PATH,
       as well as a limited set of built-in commands:

       exit
              Exit the shell.

       env
              Print the current environment variables.

       ls
              List directory contents (via external command).

OPTIONS
       simple_shell does not accept any command-line options.

LIMITATIONS
       This shell is a minimal implementation and does not support advanced
       features such as:
              - Command chaining
              - Pipes
              - Redirection
              - Wildcards
              - Full built-in command set

       Attempting to run unsupported commands or invalid syntax may result in
       an error.

EXAMPLES
              $ simple_shell
              simple_shell$ ls
              file1 file2 file3

